records.addlTxt: Atty. Angela Wang.
Preliminary hearing on January 21, 2022 at 09:15 am.

01:36 PM Defendant Michael E Harris in court, in custody, with attorney Angela Wang.    District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  The defendant is elgible for public defender representation.  Attorney Wang states they have spoken with seventeen attorneys but have been unsuccessful in obtaining counsel for the defendant.  The Court conducts colloquy with the defendant in regards to having counsel and the time limits associated with the preliminary hearing.  The Court places findings on the record and finds the defendant does not object to a short adjournment so counsel may be appointed.  The Court finds good cause for a brief adjournment and will reschedule this for a preliminary hearing and status of counsel date.  The Court notes the status of counsel date may be removed if an order appointing counsel is filed with the Court prior to that date.  Court tolled time limits for preliminary hearing.  Attorney Wang states if there is no conflict, she will likely keep this case and could be available next Friday for preliminary hearing at the 9:15 am calendar.  Bail remains as fixed.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for January 21, 2022 at 09:15 am.  Status conference scheduled for January 20, 2022 at 01:00 pm.
